Wash and dry all produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups
for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off
heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from
greens.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(you'll use the rest later), @Sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a
pinch of @salt{}.

Trim ends from @Cucumber{1%unit}. Using a #peeler{}, shave cucumber lengthwise
into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core; discard core.

Stir ribbons into bowl with vinegar mixture. Set aside, tossing occasionally,
until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}, preferably
#nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce} and
cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion
whites and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Ground Plant-Based Protein{9%ounce} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook,
breaking up into pieces, until browned and warmed through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If mixture seems dry, add a splash of water; we used 2 TBSP.

Stir in half the @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving) and
remaining vinegar. Cook for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in @Bulgogi Sauce{4%ounce}.
Bring to a simmer, then immediately turn off heat. Season again with salt and
pepper.

While plant-based protein cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}
and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings)
and season with salt and pepper; divide between bowls.

Arrange plant-based protein, carrots, and pickled cucumber on top.

> TIP: Drain any excess liquid from cucumber before adding.

Drizzle crema over everything. Garnish with scallion greens and as many
remaining sesame seeds as you like.